	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001162_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>20 Bedford Square</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">22<hi rend="sup underline">d</hi> Dec<hi rend="underline">r</hi> 1857 </p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>Captain Washington</persName></p>
<lb/><p>It has occurred to me 
<lb/>since parting that the 
<lb/>horse power of <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Laird's</persName>
<lb/>vessel is too small. 
<lb/>It would be sorry thing 
<lb/>for us to be unable 
<lb/>to stem the current in 
<lb/>the only steamer the 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001162_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'--> 
<lb/>natives ever saw. <persName>Rennies</persName>
<lb/>are with two engines 
<lb/>each having 10 H.P. 
<lb/>and they do on the 
<lb/><placeName>Thames</placeName> nicely. I mention 
<lb/>this if it is not too 
<lb/>late - and am </p>
<lb/><p rend="center">yours truly </p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
			
</div>
